- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper proposes a new clustering method and evaluates it against existing ones, which involves algorithmic analysis and comparison.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as some of the clustering techniques mentioned in the paper, such as spectral clustering, have connections to machine learning.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper may involve software implementation and optimization of the clustering algorithms.
- cs.DB (Databases) is also less likely but possible as the paper deals with graph summarization, which is a common task in database management.
